{"questionId":"22526716","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A large sample of carp from the lake is studied. The length of each fish is measured and recorded correct to the nearest <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognition to add <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>σ</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>49</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math> (cm)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22526716","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ2.7a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down the value of k.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
